history.content: Really depends on what you're looking to do in the summer. Do security if you're looking to focus on security as a part of your actual job. Otherwise, 186 would probably be better for general relevancy and if you're looking to work on any type of web app.

Hi,

I'm an incoming junior. I'm enrolled in 186 and 170, but recently I have a new interest in security so I'd like to take 161 eventually (unfortunately doing all 3 is not an option for me this semester ) . So I'm wondering if I should consider taking 161 first, in terms of how useful each class is for the Fall recruiting season and if you guys have any preference for which to take first.

Thanks
history.subject: 186 vs. 161
